    "notes": [
        "<b>Writing Intensive Courses:</b> Students must take 3 courses: 1 First Year (UWRT-150 or ISTE-110), 1 Gen Ed, & 1 program specific (CSCI-472)",
        "<b>Lab Sciences:</b> Only specific sequences are allowed in Biology, Chemistry or Physics. Please see the CS/CSEC BS/MS course page.",
        "<b>CS and CSEC Electives:</b> Only specific courses are allowed. Please see the CS and CSEC handbooks or talk to an academic advisor.",
        "<b>BS/MS Double-Counted Courses:</b> Identified with a leading *.",
        "<u><b>Swapping:</b> If approved CSEC Graduate Electives that are CSCI courses are selected as double-counts, the BS double-count can satisfy CS Elective requirements instead of Open Electives. CSEC-604 is a required MS course; however, students who have completed the related course CSCI-662 Foundations of Cryptography or undergraduate CSCI-462 Introduction to Cryptography replace CSEC-604 with an additional CSEC Graduate Elective.</u>"
    ]
